    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I allow others to query my full sync unpruned geth node.  As I am acting as a central data authority, clients want to verify the BlockHash and currently just the TransactionRoot my api returns. The clients construct a local Merkle Patricia Trie proof.  All the information for creating this proof can be gathered with a single GraphQL query if we expose the signature parameters.  If not, they have to query for the Signature parameters for each transaction in the block.",
